  "summary": "Container\nIn recent weeks, many of the Major liner owners have announced drops in their earnings, this could well be signalling that the current tonnage oversupply situation, combined with a potential gradual Red Sea return, may lead to softer container rates this year. Since Covid, rates have seen highs and moderate levels that were never achievable pre-Covid. Perhaps we will see a return to post Covid levels, unless carriers take measures such as scrapping older vessels to reduce oversupply.",
